{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782574213002,"sessionID":"ses_0f6502634ffejwxToJS3gAvgz6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_Jhcwjtzdu9NAGXwv36za04kP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"if (!(Test-Path -LiteralPath 'C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\opencode')) { exit 1 }; $matrixPatch = @'\n{\n  \"updates\": [\n    {\n      \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-commo-1f1edf8e3a-003-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata\",\n      \"set\": {\n        \"status\": \"implemented\",\n        \"targetBehavior\": \"`StartupLaunchService.resolveLaunchRoute()` and `StartupStore.resolveStartRoute()` preserve the same startup loading and start-destination contract, and `EntryAbility.onCreate()` resolves that state before `FoodikeBootstrap` renders the first route, matching the source's synchronous splash-gate behavior.\",\n        \"verificationEvidence\": [\n          \"Manual source review confirmed `SplashViewModel` exposes observable loading and start-destination state, but resolves both synchronously inside `init` before normal navigation rendering begins.\",\n          \"Manual target review confirmed `EntryAbility.onCreate()` calls `StartupLaunchService.resolveLaunchRoute(context)` before `FoodikeBootstrap` renders routes, while `StartupStore.resolveStartRoute()` keeps explicit loading and start-destination fields for the same startup handoff.\",\n          \"One bounded manual reproduction of the reported phase test command was rerun from `entry/src/test/cangjie` with the workflow env overlay after fixing the original phase-02 syntax blocker; it now fails later in `phase01_resource_theme_contract_test.cj` on `assertEqual` generic inference for `ResourceStr`, so phase-02 startup tests still do not have a PASS gate.\",\n          \"Phase 02 build gate PASS: `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-02-startup-session-navigation/build-report.md`.\"\n        ],\n        \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n 